                                    <h4>What does it mean to create a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        If you want to offer a ride to other people who want to go to the same destination as you, you can create a ride. People can then make a booking of your ride and if
                                        you accept them, you will all drive to the destination together.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>What will I get from processing a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        Our application is fully without money. It means, no one will pay you for driving him or her as well as you will not have to pay to anyone after the ride.
                                        Carpooling here is mainly about making new friendships and doing our world greener.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How to create a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        To create a ride you need to be logged in and have at least one car created in your list of cars on your personal profile page.
                                        After these two conditions are successfully completed, click on the rides page. Here you can see Add new ride button which will move you to the
                                        form for filling all the necessary information. In case you decide not to create the ride, just click on the link Back to My rides in the end of the page.
                                        Otherwise, in this one form, all the fields are required.After you fill all of them, click on Create button and you are going
                                        to be moved to List of all rides where your newly created ride is available.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Other way is to open your personal profile page by clicking on your name up on the right side and choose the My Rides option on the left side of the page.
                                        Here you can see the list of your Rides and also a button Add New Ride which will move you to the form for creating a ride. Then continue as mentioned above.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        In case you are still completely lost and have no idea how to access the form for creating a ride, here is the link but don't forget to be logged in and have a car created!<br />
                                        <a asp-page="/Rides/CreateRide">Create a ride</a>
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>Where can I see the list of my rides?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        You have to be logged in and have at least one ride created. Just open your personal profile page by clicking on
                                        your name up on the right side. On this page you can see My Rides on the left side option in which the list of rides created by you is shown.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How to edit a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        To edit a ride, you have to be logged in and have at least one ride created. Go to your personal profile page by clicking on your name up on the
                                        right side. Now on the left side choose the My rides option which shows the page with the list of all your created rides.
                                        Here in every line is a blue button with a pen inside for editing exactly that one ride. Click on that and to make sure you are editing the right one, the information are
                                        provided. If you find out you do not wish to edit this one ride, just click on the link Back To My Rides which will move you back to the list of rides.
                                        If you are sure this one is the ride you want to edit, change all the necessary information you need and click on Save Changes button. This action will
                                        move you back to the list of all rides where the information are going to be changed immediately.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another way to edit a ride is to open a page with Rides where you can see also your rides. Next to each your ride you can see the blue button with a pen inside for editing it. This
                                        button will move you to Edit Page for the ride. To make sure you are editing the right one, all the information about it are provided. If you find out you do not wish to edit this one ride, just click on the link Back To My Rides which will move you back to the list of your rides.
                                        If you are sure this one is the ride you want to edit, change all the necessary information you need and click on Save Changes button. This action will
                                        move you back to the list of all rides where the information are going to be changed immediately.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        One more way is to either open Rides Page, choose the ride you want to edit and click on details in the end of the line of the ride or choose the ride from My Rides option in your personal profile page and
                                        again, click on details in the end of the line of the ride which is supposed to be changed. Both links will move you to detailed page of your ride where on the bottom of the page you can see again button for Editing Ride.
                                        To make sure you are editing the right one, all the information about it are provided. If you find out you do not wish to edit this one ride, just click on the link Back To Rides which will move you back to the list of rides.
                                        If you are sure this one is the ride you want to edit, change all the necessary information you need and click on Save Changes button. This action will
                                        move you back to the list of all rides where the information are going to be changed immediately.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How to cancel/delete a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        To cancel a ride, you have to be logged in and have at least one ride created. Go to your personal profile page by clicking on your name up on the
                                        right side. Now on the left side choose the My rides option which shows the page with all your created rides. Each ride has on the right side of lines the red button with trash can inside for cancelling.
                                        After clicking on it you are going to be redirected to the page which asks you if you are really sure you want to delete the ride. Make sure you chose the right one by checking all the
                                        information on the current page and confirm it by clicking on Delete button. The ride will be immediately deleted and not shown for others anymore. In case you find out you do not wish to
                                        delete exactly this one ride, click on Back to My Rides link on the bottom of page and it will move you back to the list of your rides where you can choose the right one.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another way to delete a ride is to open a page with Rides where you can see also your rides. Next to each your ride you can see the red button with trash can inside for deleting it. This
                                        link will move you to Delete Page for the ride. To make sure you are deleting the right one, all the information about it are provided. If you find out you do not wish to delete this one ride, just click on the link Back To My rides which will move you back to the list of rides.
                                        If you are sure this one is the ride you want to delete click on Delete button. This action will
                                        move you back to the list of rides where the ride is not shown anymore.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        One more way is to either open Rides Page, choose the ride you want to Delete and click on details in the end of the line of the ride or choose the ride from My Rides option in your personal profile page and
                                        again, click on details in the end of the line of the ride which is supposed to be changed. Both links will move you to detailed page of your ride where on the bottom of the page you can see again button for Deleting Ride.
                                        To make sure you are deleting the right one, all the information about it are provided. Click on the Delete ride button shown on the screen and the ride will be deleted immediately.

                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>!!! With ride are deleted also all bookings connected to it. !!!</b>
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>Can I cancel the ride even if someone has booked it?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        In case the ride cannot happen because of any circumstances, you have the full right to cancel it without any fees anytime. So even if someone has booked your ride,
                                        you can still cancel it. You can find more information about how to do so in the previous question.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How do I know if someone has booked my ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        After another user books your ride, you will get a notification and also a message. All your notifications can be found under the bell next to your name up on the right side.
                                        Next to the notification bell, there are messages which will have a red circle around if you got some.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another place where you can find out if someone has booked your ride is on your personal profile page.
                                        There when you choose the My Rides option on the left side, the list of your rides is displayed. Choose the ride for which you wish to see the bookings and click on the "Bookings" link. To make sure
                                        you chose the right ride, all information are provided. Under these information, the people who has booked your ride are listed also with their booking statuses. If you wish to check the accounts, just click
                                        on their avatars (pictures).
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        One more way how to see people who has booked your ride and where you can accept or reject them is on Booking page on the top next to the page with Rides. Here you can see the list of all people who made bookings of your rides.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>Can I reject someone who booked my ride?</h4>
                                    <p>If you do not want to drive with someone because of any reasons, you have the full right to reject the person.</p>

                                    <h4>Can I reject someone even after I accepted his or her booking request?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        You are allowed to change your opinion about people who are going to drive with you anytime. So even if you have accepted someone, you can still cancel this booking of your ride. Just open the page Bookings next to the Rides page on the top of the page.
                                        Here you can see Cancel button next to the person who you accepted. After clicking on it, the passenger's bookings will be cancelled.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another way how to cancel already accepted booking is to open your personal profile page and there open My Rides section. Here click on Bookings link in the ride you want to see. Next to each person on the page are your options. If someone is accepted there
                                        you can also see Cancel button next to it. After clicking on it, the passenger's bookings will be cancelled.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How to contact people who are taking my ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        At present time, the only way to directly contact users who booked your ride, is to reply on the automatically sent booking message. It means you have to open the messages which are between your name and
                                        notification bell on the top of the page. Here you see the message from the person who booked your ride which was automatically sent. In the end of the message, there is the button Reply. After you click on it, the passengers
                                        name will appear as the person who you are going to send the message to. Now you can write what you want and just click on send button.
                                    </p>
